    p.btext I am honoured to be having my stories translated into Russian. We, in the UK, regard Russia as a great country with a rich literary history. I have always admired Russian writers, and there are so very many great ones who have been translated into English and whom I have read. Sadly, I do not come anywhere close to being as great as them, but I still hope my stories will make you, the reader in far-off Russia, smile and think about the lessons to be learned within them. Thank you for taking the time to read them, and may I also thank Katerina Komissarova for the enthusiasm and encouragement she has given me during the translation process.

